cs.CY, cs.CR, cs.LG, cs.SI, cs.AI

This paper discusses the civil rights implications of data analytics and algorithmic decision making, which falls under the category of computational social science (cs.CY) and computer vision and pattern recognition (cs.CR). The paper also proposes a research agenda for addressing these concerns, which involves building fairness into machine learning methods (cs.LG), improving transparency and control of data-driven decision making (cs.SI), and supporting cross-disciplinary scholarship (cs.AI).
